			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was going to post this under the epic robes thread, but it got a little more involved than I originally intended, so rather than hijack...
<br />

<br />
After getting player crafted robes, I'd never RVR in epic armor again, regardless of how it looks.
<br />

<br />
That said, even player crafted robes are no longer good enough.  I'm taking a break for awhile because I'm tired of being the first one dead in every combat.  Used to be if tanks saw me, I was dead.  Now if ANYONE sees me, I'm dead.  They have increased the effectiveness of every damage class, and the net result of that is that cloth casters die that much more easily.  Sure, I can get often a mez off, and maybe even save the rest of my group with it...but it won't save me...even if I'm protected and have a cleric healing only me, and that is very rare.  Sorry, I'm just not THAT altruistic.  Others in my groups were often getting as many as 2x the RPs I was getting on an outing.
<br />

<br />
Of course, short of MOC it's not like there are any realm abilities I could buy with the RPs I missed that would significantly improve my odds anyway.  Now that tanks have cheap purge, prevent flight, shield stuns and determination, sorcs, in my opinion, may as well just strap on the milk machine and stand out in emain chewing cud.  I couldn't kill a firbolg the other day even though he was fighting someone else and I lifetapped him 10 times.  Without the damage from the other person, he would have taken more still, so MOC isn't even going to do it against tanks...it would run out long before the tank went down.  
<br />

<br />
Why do we tolerate wearing cloth again?  Was it for our uber abilities?  The one that you cast once, everyone purges or group purges and then you have to wait a full minute to recast?  Oooooh uber!  They can purge it faster than I can even CAST it.  Well, I got news for you, tanks still do more damage than even wizzies do on a single target per unit time.  On top of it there are RAs to increase resists for caster damage.  Where's the increased resists against melee damage?
<br />

<br />
I'm not even sure what Mythic can do anymore to fix things.  The balance is so screwy on so many levels that I think it's gonna take alot to repair it.  I'm sure the tanks are very happy with the changes, and there are lots of them, so maybe this balance IS right for Mythic financially, since I have long suspected they've ignored the pleas of casters like sorcs because they are rare enough not to affect the bottom line much.   Even if they do figure it out, it usually takes them 6 months to attempt a fix, and up to a year to actually put in a fix that works.  
<br />

<br />
i3ullseye seemed to think we were in pretty good shape when he left.  I don't know where he got that assessment from.  I have played a sorc since day one, and I have never been more frustrated with him than I am now.   It's as I predicted months ago, only worse.  RAs for other classes improve the classes abilities in a meaninful way and at the direct expense of sorc effectiveness...determination, prevent flight, purge, and increased damage.  Sorc RAs do nothing of the sort for mind sorcs.  Thus, I predicted as the game matures, sorcs would become less and less effective.  RVR rewards now are equivalent to sorcs losing XP as they level compared to everyone else.  When they tweaked up archers and bolts, they accelerated the process.  I had no idea then how accurate I had been.  
<br />

<br />
Omyz, welcome.  I think you have a big job ahead of you, so I hope you enjoy a challenge <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Tequitus</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
