				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">By Realm Rank 5 Level 3 the following classes can have Determination 5, Ignore Pain, and Purge:
<br />
Warrior
<br />
Berserker
<br />
Savage
<br />
Blademaster
<br />
Hero
<br />
Armsman
<br />
Mercenary
<br />

<br />
This gives them 75% duration reduction to mes,stun,snare. 
<br />
Couple that with 26% resist from SC.
<br />
Add in resist buffs.
<br />
Add in purge.
<br />
Add in Ignore Pain.
<br />
What you wind up with is a list of tanks that are unable to be locked down in any way. 
<br />
They will come and kill you in just a few combat rounds, while you stand helpless, due to interrupts, to do anything about it.
<br />
BTW, MoC can be interrupted by stun (shield/style stuns from tanks work just fine to break MoC).
<br />
They also have 2x their normal hitpoints, courtesy of Ignore Pain.
<br />
The truly ambitious ones can also purchase Avoidance of Magic, to add 3% to all magic resists per level purchased.
<br />
Also consider The Empty Mind, a 10% boost to magic resistance for 60 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Face it, DAoC is a tank's game now.
<br />

<br />
I would love to be able to purchase an RA as a caster that would give me a 75% reduction to melee damage.
<br />
Or let me buy IP.
<br />
Heck, let me buy Purge for 4 points like they can...
<br />
Oh yeah, and give the buffing classes some melee resist buffs equivalent to the magic resist buffs. The AF buffs currently in the game are nowhere near the % resist to magic granted by resist buffs.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
