				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=27745&amp;sid=e7920de860e8a9135dc96eafdbc9c212#27745"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Thu Jun 19, 2003 1:55 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
				<td valign="top" align="right" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=27745&amp;sid=e7920de860e8a9135dc96eafdbc9c212"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Agreed survivability is our major problem, and of most (all?) caster classes in the 3 realms.
<br />

<br />
The problem is certainly not class specific, so we need an all caster all realm fix. This would mean a significant shift as players in all realms started or un-retired casters. In Albion and Midgard this is arguably OK, both these realms could probably handle a larger proportion of their populations being casters. But in my opionin this could seriously unbalance Hibernia: they are caster heavy already, tanks might become non-existant there after the caster improvements. 
<br />

<br />
Mythic have a nasty balancing act on their hands. To prevent the Hibernian population becoming all-caster they would have to additonally nerf the (popular) hib caster classes to prevent them becoming too appealing. This would set off even more realm balance issues... 
<br />

<br />
Sometimes I wonder if the extra interest we get from having different classes in different realms is worth the balance problems it gives rise to <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
